Remarks. This species is very similar to
Cr. muellerianae
but can be readily distinguished by lacking setae tc'' on tarsi I–IV (present in
Cr. muellerianae
), the stouter palpal segments (finer in
Cr. muellerianae
), lanceolate setae
h 1
(more palmate in
Cr. muellerianae
), and irregular dorsal reticulation (linear in
Cr. muellerianae
).
